HEADWORD: Parostosis
<hw>Par`os*to"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Para-</er>, and <er>Ostosis</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>Ossification which takes place in purely fibrous tracts; the
formation of bone outside of the periosteum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parostotic</ent>⟦br⟧
